text: Rosalind Chao (born September 23, 1957) is an American actress. Chao's best- known roles have been Soon-Lee Klinger in the mid-1980s CBS show AfterMASH, Rose Hsu Jordan in the 1993 movie The Joy Luck Club, Keiko O'Brien on Star Trek: The Next Generation and Star Trek: Deep Space Nine in the 1990s, and Dr. Kim on The O.C. in 2003. For some time, Chao worked at Disneyland as an international tour guide. ==References== Category:1957 births Category:Living people Category:American movie actors Category:American television actors Category:American voice actors Category:American stage actors Category:Actors from California Category:People from Anaheim, California
